text: Annex is an unincorporated community and census-designated place in Malheur County, Oregon, United States. Its population was 235 as of the 2010 census. The community is located on the south bank of the Snake River across from Weiser, Idaho; a bridge carrying U.S. Route 95 Spur connects the two. ==Geography== According to the U.S. Census Bureau, the community has an area of , all of it land. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Malheur County, Oregon Category:Unincorporated communities in Oregon Category:Census-designated places in Malheur County, Oregon Category:Census- designated places in Oregon
